title: Wilmeth Active Learning Center (WALC)
description: The WALC Group Study Rooms are spaces for collaborative study and group meetings. They are equipped with seating, whiteboards, and large screens with HDMI and VGA/aux connections.

title: Humanities, Social Science, and Education Library (HSSE)
description: The HSSE 145 Group Study Room is a study space intended for cooperative study and group meetings. The room includes a large table area with 8 seats and whiteboard.

title: Veterinary Medicine Library
description: The Veterinary Medical Library offers 4 small group study rooms for cooperative study and group meetings. Each room accommodates up to 5 people and has a chalkboard.

title: The Roland G. Parrish Library of Management & Economics
description: The Financial Conference room seats 11 at the conference table with 10 additional seats available. The room includes a flat-panel display and webcam with laptop compatibility.

title: John W. Hicks Undergraduate Library
description: Enjoy a variety of study spaces, including private rooms, carrels, and collaborative tables. Find reference materials and technology to support your academic journey.

title: Mathematical Sciences Library
description: The Math Library provides collections and services related to Mathematics, Computer Science, and Statistics with space for students and faculty to study, perform research, and collaborate.

title: Black Cultural Center Library
description: An ideal place for individual and group research, the BCC Library also holds a special collection of books by and about people of color as well as our own archives in addition to our main collection of books, journals, and media.

title: Aviation and Transportation Technology Library
description: The library serves as Purdue's resource for aviation information and supports the teaching and research activities of the Department of Aviation Technology.

title: Krach Leadership Center
description: The Krach Leadership Center is a satellite student union, serving as an interactive and collaborative space for students to learn and work together towards success. The facility complements the PMU and serves as a hub for collaborative work, providing additional space for conference rooms. individual study areas, and more.

title: Lawson Study Lounge
description: Located at the heart of Purdue's CS building, the Lawson Study Lounge provides a great comfortable space to study in both induvidual and group settings. The space comes with many benefits, such as great power outlet coverage and floor-to-ceiling windows that allow for good natural lighting.

title: Hall of Data Science and AI
description: Newly renovated in 2024, the DS AI building provides a copious amount of study spots, from private free-to-enter study and conference rooms to expansive collaborative spaces equipped with whiteboards that line the walls.

title: Piper's Inn @ McCutcheon
description: A favorite for late-night studying among residents, Piper's Inn provides a lively environment to study, especially with friends. The place comes equipped with a vending machine for late-night snacking!

title: Cary Quad URSC
description: This is a comfortable space that provides an opportunity for students to work individually or in groups. A few components of the collaborative space include: dry erase board tables, ceiling to floor dry erase boards, four audiovisual (AV) monitors, and awesome furniture.

title: West Lafayette Public Library
description: The West Lafayette Public Library is a full-service public library serving the residents of West Lafayette. This library is one of the quietest study spots available in West Lafayette, comes equipped with free-to-use computers and bookable meeting rooms
